## 2. Site Architecture — 7 Pages

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["🏠 Home"] --> B["📋 About Us"]
    A --> C["🛠️ Services"]
    A --> D["🗺️ Interactive Map"]
    A --> E["💬 Testimonials"]
    A --> F["💰 Pricing"]
    A --> G["📞 Contact"]
```

### Page Breakdown

#### 2.1 Home (Landing Page)
- Hero section with full-width banner, tagline, and CTA buttons
- Tagline: *"Turning Spatial Data into Real-World Solutions"*
- Quick overview cards for 3 service pillars (Flood & Environmental, Land & Urban Planning, GIS Mapping)
- "Meet the Team" teaser with photos + names linking to About
- Stats counter section (e.g., "50+ Projects Delivered", "10+ Districts Served")
- CTA banner → Contact / Pricing

#### 2.2 About Us
- Company story and mission statement
- Individual profiles for both partners:
  - **Sambus Geospatial (Emmanuel Yerbo):** BSc Geography & Regional Planning, UCC. GeoAI, Flood Mapping, Remote Sensing specialist.
  - **AcuGeospatial (Gifty Gyamera-Annor):** GIS Mapping, Land Use Analysis, Spatial Data Support specialist.
- Certifications & tools grid (ESRI certs, ArcGIS, QGIS, GEE, Pix4D logos)
- "Who We Work With" section (NGOs, Government, Real Estate, Researchers)

#### 2.3 Services
- Three service category cards with expand/detail views:
  1. **Flood & Environmental** — Flood Risk Mapping, Environmental Change Detection, Water Risk Analysis
  2. **Land & Urban Planning** — Land Use/Cover Mapping, Site Suitability Analysis, Urban Expansion Analysis
  3. **GIS Mapping & Data Support** — Map Design for Reports, Research & Thesis GIS Support, Spatial Data Analysis
- Each service includes: description, sample deliverable image, key tools used

#### 2.4 Interactive Map (GEE Flood Vulnerability Rater)
- **Embedded Google Earth Engine application** showing the Volta Region flood susceptibility map
- Layer toggles: Elevation, Slope, HAND, Flood Frequency, LULC, Distance to Water
- Color-coded risk zones (green → yellow → red)
- Click-to-query: user clicks a location and gets a flood vulnerability rating (Low/Medium/High)
- Info panel explaining the 6 conditioning factors and methodology
- Link to the full research paper / writing sample

#### 2.5 Testimonials
- Placeholder testimonial cards (3–4 entries) with:
  - Client name, organization, role (placeholder)
  - Quote text (placeholder)
  - Star rating
  - Project type tag
- Carousel/slider layout
- CTA: "Want to be our next success story?"

#### 2.6 Pricing
- Three-tier pricing cards:
  1. **Basic** — Single map production, report-ready output
  2. **Standard** — Multi-layer analysis, site suitability or flood mapping
  3. **Premium** — Full project: data collection, analysis, interactive deliverables
- "Custom Quote" option with contact form link
- FAQ accordion (turnaround times, data requirements, revision policy)

#### 2.7 Contact
- Contact form (Name, Email, Organization, Service Interest dropdown, Message)
- Direct contact info for both partners (email, phone)
- Embedded Google Maps showing location (Cape Coast, Ghana)
- Social links (LinkedIn, GitHub)

