## 6. GEE Interactive Map — Technical Approach

The centerpiece feature: an embedded Google Earth Engine flood vulnerability rater.

### Implementation Options

**Option A — GEE App Embed (Recommended for Phase 1)**
- Build the flood susceptibility viewer as a GEE App via `ui.Map()` and `ui.Panel()`
- Publish via `ee.apps` and embed in an `<iframe>` on the Maps page
- Pros: Fastest to implement, uses existing GEE code
- Cons: Limited custom styling, GEE UI constraints

**Option B — Custom Leaflet/MapLibre + GEE Tiles (Phase 2)**
- Export GEE layers as Cloud Optimized GeoTIFFs or tile services
- Build custom map interface with Leaflet.js or MapLibre GL
- Full UI control, custom popups, branded styling
- More development time but superior UX

### Map Features (Phase 1)
- [x] Flood susceptibility layer (3-class: Low/Medium/High)
- [x] Click-to-query vulnerability rating
- [x] Layer toggle panel
- [x] Legend with risk color coding
- [x] Info panel with methodology summary
- [ ] Town-level zoom insets (Phase 2)
- [ ] Downloadable reports per location (Phase 2)

